subsection.p:
These steps must be undertaken in this order, as the rotation matrix only rotates around the origin. This is what's going on, mathematically: 

          (x_{cr}(t), y_{cr}(t)) \amp = \begin{bmatrix} cos(a) & -sin(a) \\ sin(a) & \text{ }cos(a) \end{bmatrix} \left( \begin{bmatrix} x_{c}(t) \\ y_{c}(t) \end{bmatrix} - \begin{bmatrix} x_0 \\ y_0 \end{bmatrix} \right) + \begin{bmatrix} x_0 \\ y_0 \end{bmatrix}
          \amp = \begin{bmatrix} (x_{c}(t) - x_0)\cos(a) - (y_{c}(t) - y_0)\sin(a) + x_0 \\ (x_{c}(t)- x_0)\sin(a) + (y_{c}(t) - y_0)\cos(a) + y_0 \end{bmatrix}.
